{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol\/getWeekNumberingYear()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol"]]},"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE20getWeekNumberingYearSiyF","title":"getWeekNumberingYear()","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"getWeekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"text":" falls.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"getWeekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This function, taken together with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_date_time_get_day_of_week()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can be used to determine the full ISO","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"week date on which ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"text":" falls.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is usually equal to the normal Gregorian year (as returned by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_date_time_get_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), except as detailed below:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Thursday, the week-numbering year is always equal to the usual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year.  For other days, the number is such that every day"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"within a complete week (Monday to Sunday) is contained within the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"same week-numbering year.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday occurring near the end of the year,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one greater than the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring early in the next year)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Friday, Saturday and Sunday occurring near the start of the year,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one less than the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring late in the previous year)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An equivalent description is that the week-numbering year is equal to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the calendar year containing the majority of the days in the current"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"week (Monday to Sunday)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that January 1 0001 in the proleptic Gregorian calendar is a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Monday, so this function never returns 0."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeprotocol\/getweeknumberingyear()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeProtocol":{"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DateTimeProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeprotocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DateTimeProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"DateTimeProtocol","abstract":[{"code":"GDateTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"into a single structure."}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeProtocol/getWeekNumberingYear()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeprotocol\/getweeknumberingyear()","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeProtocol\/getWeekNumberingYear()","type":"topic","role":"symbol","title":"getWeekNumberingYear()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getWeekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}}}